SD Reader/Writer + AES (Single-Sector Demo Flow)
================================================

Final demo flow
---------------
All 3 results are kept in ONE selected sector.

Buttons:
- BTNC: write plain digit from SW4_1
- BTNU: encrypt current plain block
- BTNR: decrypt current encrypted block
- BTNL: clear payload
- BTND: reset

Switches:
- SW15_5: choose sector index (0..2047)
- SW4_1: digit nibble
- SW0: unused

Sector layout (same selected sector)
------------------------------------
- bytes 0..15   : plain
- bytes 16..31  : encrypted
- bytes 32..47  : decrypted
- bytes 48..511 : 00

Seven segment
-------------
- After BTNC: shows plain nibble
- After BTNU: shows encrypted nibble
- After BTNR: shows decrypted nibble

LED mapping
-----------
- LED[1] write done
- LED[2] encrypt done
- LED[3] decrypt done
- LED[4] clear done
- LED[6] busy

FPGA demonstration (exact)
--------------------------
1) Rebuild bitstream and reprogram FPGA.
2) Set SW15_5=0, set SW4_1=3, press BTNC.
3) Keep SW15_5=0, press BTNU.
4) Keep SW15_5=0, press BTNR.
5) After each press, wait for LED[6] busy to turn OFF.

PC verification
---------------
Run as Administrator:

python verify_sd.py \\.\PhysicalDrive1 0

Check:
- Plain [0..15]
- Enc [16..31]
- Dec [32..47]
